  "prompt": "How do you check an AT&T balance?",
  "response": "To check your AT&T balance, you can use several methods:\n\n1. **AT&T Website:**\n   - Go to the AT&T website and log in to your account using your username and password. Once logged in, your account balance will be displayed on the dashboard.\n\n2. **AT&T Mobile App:**\n   - Download the AT&T app from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store. Log in with your AT&T credentials, and you can view your account balance and usage details directly in the app.\n\n3. **Text Message:**\n   - You can text \"BAL\" to 615-555 to receive your account balance via text message.\n\n4. **Calling Customer Service:**\n   - Dial 611 from your AT&T mobile phone or 1-800-331-0500 from any phone to reach customer service, where you can inquire about your balance.\n\n5. **Billing Statement:**\n   - If you receive a paper or electronic billing statement, your account balance will be listed there as well.\n\nChoose the method that is most convenient for you!",
